Paper: hep-th/9508149

Date: 1995-08-28

Title: Chaos Suppression in the SU(2) Yang--Mills--Higgs System

Comments: LaTex, 10 pages, to be published in Phys. Rev. D

Journal-ref: Phys.Rev. D52 (1995) 6189-6191

We study the classical chaos--order transition in the spatially homogenousSU(2) Yang--Mills--Higgs system by using a quantal analog of Chirikov'sresonance overlap criterion. We obtain an analytical estimation of the range ofparameters for which there is chaos suppression.